    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individue Trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina favente gratia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Ufficium pietatis ac religionis semper
                        duximus, quatenus hominibus sanctis et divino mancipatis ministerio
                        providere ad solatium animae nostrae redundet. Quocirca noverit omnium
                        fidelium regni nostri nostrorumque praesentium ac futurorum industria,
                        quomodo <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Troilus/Volongus">Troilus Volongus</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Pamphilus">Pamphilus</name></persName> de Lanternis, <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Embassies/ambassadors"
                            >legati</rs>
                        <rs
                            key="#Village/castle_representatives #Urban_communities #Rural_communities"
                            >comunitatis nostrae</rs> de <placeName ref="#places/1834"
                            >Lonado</placeName>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/312"><rs key="#Comitatus"
                                >comitatus</rs> Brixie</geogName>, adstantes ante serenitatem
                        nostram exposuerint damna, cedes et expoliationes, quas fideles nostri passi
                        sunt ex incendiis et excursionibus Hungarorum. Quapropter petierunt
                        humiliter in nomine <persName key="#Archpriests"><name ref="Lupus"
                                >Lupi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archpriests">archipresbyteri</rs> totius cleri et universae <rs
                            key="#Plebs">plebis</rs> illius loci, ut, cum iam immineat Barbarorum
                        rabies, liceat ipsis <rs key="#Incastellamento">construere et reedificare
                                <rs key="#Defensive_elements">propugnacula</rs> et <rs key="#Walls"
                                >muros</rs></rs>, quibus tueri possint fideles et res sanctas. Nos
                        animadvertentes preces sanctorum illorum virorum et totius populi qui nobis
                        et regno nostro semper fideles extiterunt, benigne supplicationibus eorum
                        nobis humiliter porrectis annuimus et decernimus et nostra auctoritate
                        roboramus, ut imminente necessitate ac Paganorum incursu reedificentur <rs
                            key="#Walls">muri</rs> et <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Tower">turribus</rs> et <rs key="#Defensive_elements"
                            >fortiliciis</rs> et <rs key="#Clusae/gates">portis</rs>. Item
                        potestatem habeant construere turres circa vel supra <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Castle #Tower #Clusae/gates #Walls #Defensive_elements #Incastellamento #Churches"
                            >Sanctorum Ioannis Baptiste et Zenonis martyris</orgName> in defensione
                            <rs key="#Plebs">plebis</rs>, ecclesie et sactarum rerum et in loco et
                        ubicumque archipresbyter Lupus necessarium duxerit. Si quis igitur fideles
                        nostros perturbare aut quovis modo huic nostrae paginae adversari ausus
                        fuerit, <rs key="#Penalty">octuaginta libras auri optimi componere
                            cogatur</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem regiae nostrae
                            camere</rs> et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">reliquam
                            partem ecclesiae Sanctorum Ioannis Baptistae et Zenonis martyris</rs>
                        ipsius loci patroni. Ut vero firmior credatur et processu temporis
                        stabilitatem obtineat, manu nostra roboramus et anulo nostro segnamus.
                        Signum domni (M) Berengarii serenissimi regis. <persName key="#Chancellor"
                            ref="#people/1501">Ioannes</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi</persName>
                        episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovi. Datum
                            <placeName ref="#places/59">Veronae</placeName> III idus mai, anno
                        dominicae incarnationis DCCCCIX, domini vero Berengarii regis XXII,
                        indictione VI.</ab>
                </div>
